**Using JAVA inbuilt function of Binary Search:**

**Ques:** What does the Arrays.binarySearch() function returns?
**Ans:** If the target element is present in the array then return the index of that element. But if not present then return the index where it should have been if it was peresent but in some different way.
**If the target element was to present at index i then it will return (-i-1) i.e., if 2 is the index then it will return -3.**

```
class Solution {
    public int searchInsert(int[] arr, int target) {

        int index = Arrays.binarySearch(arr,target);
        return index<0 ? -(index+1) : index;
    }
}
```

