**One line code using Lower Bound of STL**
What is lower bound in array?
Each element of an array stores one value and is referenced by its index (coordinate position). The index of the first element of an array is called its lower bound. Function returns the index of the next smallest number just smaller than or equal to that number. 

```
    int searchInsert(vector<int>& nums, int target) {
        return lower_bound(nums.begin(), nums.end(), target) - nums.begin();
    }
```

