# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
The given code is a solution to the Search Insert Position problem, which requires finding the index of the target element in a sorted array, or the index where it should be inserted if it is not present in the array.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
I just used the most basic brute force approach which came to my mind.


# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int searchInsert(int[] nums, int target) {
        for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++){
            if(nums[i]==target){
                return i;
            }else{
                if(target<nums[0]){
                    return 0;
                }else if(target>nums[nums.length-1]){
                    return nums.length;
                }else if(i>0 && nums[i-1]<target && target<nums[i]){
                    return i;
                }
            }
        }
        return -1;
    }
}
```
